results.name: Permutation of natural numbers: a(n) = A064989(A250469(n)).
link: Antti Karttunen, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
Index entries for sequences that are permutations of the natural numbers
formula: As a composition of related permutations:
A000035(a(n)) = A000035(n). [This permutation preserves the parity of n.]
A020639(a(n)) = A020639(n). [More generally, it preserves the smallest prime dividing n.]
mathematica: f[n_] := Times @@ Power[Which[# == 1, 1, # == 2, 1, True, NextPrime[#, -1]] & /@ First@ #, Last@ #] &@ Transpose@ FactorInteger@ n; g[n_] := If[n == 1, 0, PrimePi@ FactorInteger[n][[1, 1]]]; Function[s, MapIndexed[ Function[{m, n}, f[Lookup[s, g[n] + 1][[m]] - Boole[n == 1]]][#1, First@ #2] &, #] &@ Map[Position[Lookup[s, g@ #], #][[1, 1]] &, Range@ 120]]@ PositionIndex@ Array[g, 10^4] (* _Michael De Vlieger_, Mar 09 2017, Version 10 *)
xref: Related permutations: A266403, A266416, A249817, A249818.
